abstract: New York Rangers goaltender Henrik Lundqvist is cleared to return to practice after sustaining blood-vessel injury when he was hit in throat by puck.
lead_paragraph: Lundqvist was scheduled to participate in his first practice since being injured Feb. 2, but he did not participate in the team’s workout because his wife was close to giving birth to their second child.

headline.main: Henrik Lundqvist Loses Practice Time but Gains a Daughter
